title: Space Force funds experiment on use of AI to predict satellite failures
summary: RS21, a data science startup developing artificial intelligence tools for autonomous space operations, won a U.S. Space Force contract to research the use of AI to predict satellite failures in orbit.

title: NASA Prepares to Say 'Farewell' to InSight Spacecraft
summary: A closer look at what goes into wrapping up the mission as the spacecraft’s power supply continues to dwindle.

title: SpaceX successfully launches its first Falcon Heavy in 40 months
summary: SpaceX now has one more landing—51—than launches this year.

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy launches first U.S. national security mission
summary: A SpaceX Falcon Heavy lifted off Nov. 1 at 9:41 a.m. Eastern from Launch Complex 39A at the Kennedy Space Center, Florida, carrying the U.S. Space Force USSF-44 mission to geostationary Earth orbit.

title: Japanese lunar lander, with NASA rideshare, to launch this month
summary: Japanese lunar lander developer ispace is in the final phases of preparations for the launch of its first lunar lander mission, a flight that will include a NASA lunar cubesat mission as a secondary payload.

title: New guidance from Space Force acquisition boss: ‘The traditional ways must be reformed’
summary: In an Oct. 31 memo, Calvelli laid out nine “space acquisition tenets” intended to drive change in the procurement of space systems

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy lofts USSF-44 on first flight in three years
summary: The world’s most powerful operational rocket, SpaceX’s Falcon Heavy, took to the Florida skies for the first time in over three years November 1 for the USSF-44 mission, a US Space Force contracted flight with a classified payload and at least one rideshare satellite..

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket rolls to pad for Tuesday launch, dual booster landing
summary: A SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket has rolled out to Kennedy Space Center Pad 39A for its first launch (and dual booster landing)...

title: Arianespace partners with Australian space tug startup
summary: Arianespace is exploring the compatibility of its rockets with orbital transfer vehicles being developed by Space Machines Company, an Australian startup.

title: Falcon Heavy rocket on the launch pad for one of SpaceX’s most complex missions
summary: The first Falcon Heavy rocket flight in more than three years is scheduled Tuesday from Florida’s Space Coast to begin SpaceX’s longest-duration launch mission to date, a roughly six-hour climb into geosynchronous orbit more than 20,000 miles over the equator with a bundle of U.S. Space Force payloads. The powerful rocket’s two reusable side boosters will return to Cape Canaveral for landing.
